      "acceptanceCriteria": "Software QA documentation must include version control, regression testing, and traceability to requirements at Gradation 4 for MRL 5 Class III device.",
      "rationale": "Version control and basic regression tests are in place but formal traceability to device requirements and independent code review are absent. Achieved level falls two gradations below required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy testing and method of manufactured solutions must be demonstrated for all governing equations relevant to hemolysis transport at Gradation 4.",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy studies were performed only for the primary flow solver; the scalar hemolysis transport equation was not independently verified. Achieved level is insufficient for MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation or equivalent grid convergence study must demonstrate discretization error below 5% on hemolysis index QoI at Gradation 4.",
      "rationale": "A three-level grid convergence study was completed; observed convergence rate is acceptable but discretization error on the hemolysis scalar exceeds the 5% threshold at the finest mesh tested, leaving achieved level at 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must replicate all five VAD operating points including hematocrit, temperature, and blood analogue rheology at Gradation 5.",
      "rationale": "Bench experiments used bovine blood at three of five target operating points; hematocrit variability and temperature control records are incomplete for two points. Gap of two gradations identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E_rel) must be computed with uncertainty bounds for all QoIs at all operating points at Gradation 5.",
      "rationale": "Relative error computed for three operating points without uncertainty bounds; two operating points lack experimental comparators entirely. Achieved level severely below required for Class III absolute hemolysis claim."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation must directly correspond to the absolute hemolysis index required by the COU decision at Gradation 4.",
      "rationale": "Normalized hemolysis index (NIH) is used in validation while the COU requires absolute hemolysis index (AHI); the mapping between the two is documented but introduces additional uncertainty not fully quantified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
